author: @sadecechaewonn
text:
Dear Chaewon,

Whenever I whisper your name, a gentle breeze stirs within me,
Soft like a leaf, yet unshakable like a tree rooted deep in the earth.
There is a hidden poem in your eyes,
A verse rewritten with every glance, read only by me.

Sometimes, I watch the world from a quiet room,
Where even the noise of the crowd loses its meaning as I think of you.
I imagine a smile upon your lips,
And even that dream outshines the stars at night.

Know that this love blooming inside me for you
Will not bow to time nor seasons.
It puts even spring to shame, for it cannot rival your smile.
And I, I will always be a word that belongs to you,
A word longing to find meaning in your sentences.

If one day you read these lines,
Please understand that even in my most silent moments,
I was speaking with your voice inside my heart.
And every poem, every song, every breath
Was, in truth, a letter written for you.

Even if you never notice, I will always say,
Chaewon, I loved you like a poem,
And I have hidden your name in every verse.
